<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Eat Bread at a Dinner Party</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">The bread !</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="contrast">Often it &apos;s the first source of sustenance for a starving dinner guest</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1003" relname="contrast">but wait !</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1002" relname="joint">Not so fast !</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1002" relname="joint">Is it rude to start breaking it open</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1008" relname="span">and chowing down</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="7" relname="circumstance">before you &apos;re even seated ? !</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1010" relname="span">There is basic etiquette</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="9" relname="elaboration">attached to eating bread at the dinner table .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1012" relname="span">This article only deals with etiquette</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="11" relname="elaboration">relevant to some anglophone cultures .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1013" relname="span">It is possible other cultural requirements exist</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1014" relname="span">for eating bread in other parts of the world -</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="span">asking first is a good idea</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="15" relname="condition">if you do n&apos;t know !</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1017" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1017" relname="joint">Wait before breaking bread .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1020" relname="contrast">It is quite possible that you &apos;re starving ,</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="span">but it is ill-mannered</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1022" relname="span">to eat the bread without respite</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="21" relname="circumstance">before the first course arrives at the table .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1025" relname="condition">If bread is sitting on the table already ,</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1025" relname="span">wait until the first course is served</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="24" relname="circumstance">before helping yourself to it .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1028" relname="condition">If bread is handed out by a waiter ,</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">allow the waiter to use bread tongs</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="27" relname="purpose">to place it on the plate .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1017" relname="joint">Do not be tempted to stick your hand into the waiter &apos;s basket</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1031" relname="span">and grab more !</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="30" relname="elaboration">Ask instead .</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1017" relname="joint">And again , wait until everyone has started eating .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1034" relname="preparation">Eat the bread carefully .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1036" relname="span">A dinner party is not the time</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="34" relname="purpose">to display breakfast table bread habits .</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1037" relname="span">Instead , break apart the bread into small pieces</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="36" relname="means">using your fingers .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1039" relname="contrast">Do not cut the bread</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1039" relname="contrast">or bite into the large part of the bread .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1042" relname="condition">If you wish to add butter to your bread ,</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1042" relname="span">add it to each small piece</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="41" relname="circumstance">after you have broken it .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1043" relname="span">Place the broken bread onto the bread and butter plate .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1045" relname="joint">This small plate is found just above the dinner plate</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">and is used</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="45" relname="purpose">to hold the bread and butter .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="preparation">Using your bread ,</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1048" relname="joint">place a small bit of butter onto the bread and butter plate next to your bread .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1049" relname="joint">Do not &quot; double dip &quot; into the butter dish .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1051" relname="joint">Take only what you need from the butter dish</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="joint">and place that onto the plate .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1053" relname="span">Carefully add neatly spread butter onto your hand</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="52" relname="elaboration">broken pieces of bread with your hands .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1054" relname="joint">Beware the bread bloat .</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1057" relname="concession">While some people are very careful not to overdo the bread ,</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="joint">others consume too much at the dinner table</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1057" relname="joint">and cannot eat all of their meal .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1059" relname="preparation">Avoid this</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="60" relname="attribution">by remembering</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="span">that bread is the support cast and not the star .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="62" relname="condition">If you &apos;re still starving later ,</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1061" relname="span">you can raid the fridge at home , out of sight .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1064" relname="span">Note that many functions such as weddings , conferences , etc. , will only cater for enough bread</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="64" relname="purpose">to go around per person once .</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1063" relname="joint">If you ask for additional bread</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1063" relname="joint">and it is refused for this reason ,</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1068" relname="span">do n&apos;t despair</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="68" relname="elaboration">( and equally , do n&apos;t take it out on the poor waiter ) .</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="span">The best thing</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1071" relname="span">to do is to ask</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="73" relname="condition">if the waiter can return to you with more bread</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1072" relname="span">if any is left over .</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1074" relname="span">There are always people on low-carb diets , etc. ,</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="74" relname="elaboration">who refuse their share of bread .</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="77" relname="condition">If you have special dietary needs , allergies , etc. ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1077" relname="span">such as not consuming dairy or gluten ,</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1078" relname="same_unit">ask the waiter quietly at an opportune moment</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="1080" relname="condition">if the bread ingredients are known ;</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="81" relname="attribution">be clear</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1080" relname="span">that you have an allergy or dietary issue with certain ingredients .</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="83" relname="condition">If it cannot be ascertained with certainty or ease ,</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1081" relname="span">simply refuse the bread politely .</segment>
